reviews.text:
Your traditional cha chaan teng in Hong Kong. They serve a whole range of food to you to choose from.

I order the fried rice noodles with pork. It tasted delicious but was a little on the oily side. But the flavor was good and I would definitely recommend it.

As for the service, the waiters and cashier was not very friendly. It could be because I did not know how to speak Cantonese.

But overall a great place to eat. Also note that I think they do not have an English menu.
general taste, big size. speedy. :-)
Classic Hong Kong diner style. Good food, fast and at a good rate.
Just a simple breakfast place to get delicious congee.
Only walking.

reviews.text: Nice Wonton noodles soup, spacious dining area and clean washroom.
I had the worst corned beef and egg sandwich in my life here. It's such a simple dish and they managed to screw it up. They served the corned beef raw which for me is unexpected and unacceptable.

Not really recommend this place, although very nearby Ibis hotel. Food is average and suprisingly staff's attitude is ok. However the old lady who wear spec at the counter is very rude and no manners at all! When my dad went to pay the bill, she even cover her mouth with hand seems my dad is a somekind of germs??? What the hell?! Speechless with her attitude. More choices available in Hong Kong not necessary to go this restaurant.

reviews.text: 出品算ok有粥有粉麵∼可惜佢d餐千年不變

櫃檯人員服務態度極差。
連要給一顆星都嫌多。如果您聽不懂中文或英文，也不應該讓客人感覺尷尬不舒服。客人來你餐廳不是來受氣的。

2.5개의 별이 적당할 듯 한데..
홍콩의 김밥천국이라는 별명이 있는듯 한데..
그 정도를 기대하면 될 듯.

새우볶음밥(HKD 47) 굴소스채소(HKD 21) 주문.
새우볶음밥의 양이 많다. 2명이 함께 나누어도 될 듯.
채소는 굴소스를 곁들여 무난한 맛.
下午茶完全唔得， 炸醬肉好硬骨骨， 麵硬掘掘， 湯飲咗啖吐返出嚟， 咖啡正常． 其它冇食過不評論

幾年前來香港時，剛好住對面的ibis hotel，曾來過這家吃雲吞麵，印象中湯鮮味美，雲吞大顆蝦味濃厚。

這次訪港旅遊，特地來回味一下，晚間消夜時段點了個三拼的雲吞麵，牛肉片+雲吞+牛肉丸，主料都很不錯吃，可惜不知道甚麼湯頭有苦味，看似由配菜散發出來的，跟印象中美好的滋味有些落差。

也許記憶中當時心情太興奮，吃甚麼都特美味吧~

不過這家還是很推薦各位朋友來吃點東西，餐廳乾淨衛生，座位舒適，早餐到消夜都有賣餐食，而且價位與排隊名店相比之下，便宜許多，下次訪港旅遊一樣會再去吃一次~

음식은 soso.
밥 빨리나오고
양도 많습니다.
식탁옆 서랍에 스푼, 냅킨 등 들어있어요.

밀크티에 얼음넣은거고,
레몬들어간 아이스티를 먹으려면

많이들 혼동하는지 직원이 설명해줘서 수정해서 주문했어요.
冷氣待修！合怕冷者！

Your traditional cha chaan teng in Hong Kong. They serve a whole range of food to you to choose from.

I order the fried rice noodles with pork. It tasted delicious but was a little on the oily side. But the flavor was good and I would definitely recommend it.

As for the service, the waiters and cashier was not very friendly. It could be because I did not know how to speak Cantonese.

But overall a great place to eat. Also note that I think they do not have an English menu.
凍檸茶好喝、蝦類餐點不錯、牛肉嫩，廁所乾淨一點會更好
